how do i install the img

How I installed on my Garmin 350...I took a 2gb sd card and formatted it to FAT32. Next, within the sd card I created a folder called "Garmin". Last I dragged and dropped the downloaded img file to that folder. Its already unlocked. Thats all! Once its transfered to the Garmin unit, go into the setting and check the newly imported map and uncheck the older one.

This worked great once I made a slight change on how to do this on my nuvi265wt. 
1) Simply create a folder named "Gramin" on a 2gb SD card (Not SDHC). Make sure this card is completely empty.
2)Transfer the the zip file from your hardrive to the SD card and place it in the "Garmin" folder (you dont have to unzip or unrar this file, leave it alone)
3) Rename the file on the SD card "gmapsupp", (for me I did not add the .img extension, tried it first and didn't work, removed it and it worked)
4) Now enjoy having to 2011 maps!

5) Then just add the SD card to your garmin while its turned off.
6) Turn it on then go to tools-settings-maps-maps info, then check the 2011 maps and uncheck whatever old map you are using.
7) You must have the SD card in the GPS in order to use the maps, now enjoy
